SIMPLE: present
RECORDS: 6

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Present
<hw>Pres"ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧sent</ets>, L. <ets>praesens</ets>,<ets>-entis</ets>,
that is before one, in sight or at hand, p. p. of <ets>praeesse</ets> to
be before; <ets>prae</ets> before + <ets>esse</ets> to be. See
<er>Essence</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Being at hand, within reach or call, within certain
contemplated limits; -- opposed to <xex>absent</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These things have I spoken unto you, being yet <qex>present</qex>
with you.</q> <rj><qau>John xiv. 25.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Now existing, or in process; begun but not ended;
now in view, or under consideration; being at this time; not past or
future; <as>as, the <ex>present</ex> session of Congress; the
<ex>present</ex> state of affairs; the <ex>present</ex>
instance.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I'll bring thee to the <qex>present</qex> business</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not delayed; immediate; instant; coincident.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>present</xex> recompense.⟦rdquo⟧ ⟦ldquo⟧A
<xex>present</xex> pardon.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An ambassador . . . desires a <qex>present</qex> audience.</q>
<rj><qau>Massinger.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Ready; quick in emergency; as a <xex>present</xex>
wit.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Favorably attentive; propitious.</def>
<mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To find a god so <qex>present</qex> to my prayer.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Present tense</b></col> <fld>(Gram.)</fld>, <cd>the tense
or form of a verb which expresses action or being in the present time;
as, I <xex>am writing</xex>, I <xex>write</xex>, or I <xex>do
write</xex>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Present</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Present
<hw>Pres"ent</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>pr⟦eacute⟧sent</ets>.
See <er>Present</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Present
time; the time being; time in progress now, or at the moment
contemplated; as, at this <xex>present</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Past and <qex>present</qex>, wound in one.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Present letters or
instrument, as a deed of conveyance, a lease, letter of attorney, or
other writing; as in the phrase, ⟦ldquo⟧ Know all men by these
<xex>presents</xex>,⟦rdquo⟧ that is, by the writing itself, ⟦ldquo⟧ per
has literas <xex>praesentes</xex>; ⟦rdquo⟧ -- in this sense, rarely used
in the singular.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>A present tense, or the form of
the verb denoting the present tense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>At present</b></col>, <cd>at the present time; now.</cd>
-- <col><b>For the present</b></col>, <cd>for the tine being;
temporarily.</cd> -- <col><b>In present</b></col>, <cd>at once, without
delay.</cd> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧With them, <xex>in present</xex>,
half his kingdom; the rest to follow at his death.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Milton.</au></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Present</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Present
<hw>Pre*sent"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Presented</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Presenting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧senter</ets>, L. <ets>praesentare</ets>, fr.
<ets>praesens</ets>, a. See <er>Present</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To bring or introduce into the presence of some one,
especially of a superior; to introduce formally; to offer for
acquaintance; <as>as, to <ex>present</ex> an envoy to the king</as>;
(with the reciprocal pronoun) to come into the presence of a
superior.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Now there was a day when the sons of God came to
<qex>present</qex> themselves before the lord.</q> <rj><qau>Job i.
6</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To exhibit or offer to view or notice; to lay before
one's perception or cognizance; to set forth; to <xex>present</xex> a
fine appearance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lectorides's memory is ever . . . <qex>presenting</qex> him with
the thoughts of other persons.</q> <rj><qau>I. Watts.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To pass over, esp. in a ceremonious manner; to give
in charge or possession; to deliver; to make over.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So ladies in romance assist their knight,⟦br⟧
<qex>Present</qex> the spear, and arm him for the fight.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To make a gift of; to bestow; to give, generally in
a formal or ceremonious manner; to grant; to confer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My last, least offering, I <qex>present</qex> thee now.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Hence: To endow; to bestow a gift upon; to favor, as
with a donation; also, to court by gifts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Octavia <qex>presented</qex> the poet for him admirable elegy on
her son Marcellus.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>To present; to personate.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>7.</sn> In specific uses; <sd>(a)</sd> <def>To nominate to an
ecclesiastical benefice; to offer to the bishop or ordinary as a
candidate for institution.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The patron of a church may <qex>present</qex> his clerk to a
parsonage or vicarage; that is, may offer him to the bishop of the
diocese to be instituted.</q> <rj><qau>Blackstone.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(b)</sd> <def>To nominate for support at a public school or other
institution .</def> <au>Lamb.</au> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>To lay before a
public body, or an official, for consideration, as before a legislature,
a court of judicature, a corporation, etc.; <as>as, to <ex>present</ex>
a memorial, petition, remonstrance, or indictment</as>.</def>
<sd>(d)</sd> <def>To lay before a court as an object of inquiry; to give
notice officially of, as a crime of offence; to find or represent
judicially; <as>as, a grand jury <ex>present</ex> certain offenses or
nuisances, or whatever they think to be public injuries</as>.</def>
<sd>(e)</sd> <def>To bring an indictment against .</def>
<mark>[U.S]</mark> <sd>(f)</sd> <def>To aim, point, or direct, as a
weapon; <as>as, to <ex>present</ex> a pistol or the point of a sword to
the breast of another</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pesent arms</b></col> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>, <cd>the command
in response to which the gun is carried perpendicularly in front of the
center of the body, and held there with the left hand grasping it at the
lower band, and the right hand grasping the small of the stock, in token
of respect, as in saluting a superior officer; also, the position taken
at such a command.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Present</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Present
<hw>Pre*sent"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>To appear at
the mouth of the uterus so as to be perceptible to the finger in vaginal
examination; -- said of a part of an infant during labor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Present</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 5 ====
HEADWORD: Present
<hw>Pres"ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧sent</ets> .]</ety> <def>Anything presented or given; a
gift; a donative; <as>as, a Christmas <ex>present</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Gift; donation; donative; benefaction. See
<er>Gift</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Present</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 6 ====
HEADWORD: Present
<hw>Pre*sent"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>
<def>The position of a soldier in presenting arms; <as>as, to stand at
<ex>present</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Presentable</ent>⟦br⟧
